# CodeDNA v0.3

This project uses the CodeDNA annotation standard.

Every source file begins with:
# === CODEDNA:0.3 =============================================
# FILE: filename.ext
# PURPOSE: what it does (≤15 words)  
# CONTEXT_BUDGET: always | normal | minimal
# DEPENDS_ON: file → symbol | none
# EXPORTS: symbol(args) → return_type
# LAST_MODIFIED: ≤8 words
# ==============================================================

EDITING RULES:
1. Update LAST_MODIFIED first
2. Check DEPENDS_ON before changing function signatures  
3. Follow @REQUIRES-READ annotations before writing logic
4. Apply @MODIFIES-ALSO cascades in the same edit

GENERATION RULES:
1. Manifest header before any imports
2. @REQUIRES-READ on cross-file functions
3. Semantic variable names: list_dict_X_from_db not data

EXPORTS = contracts. Do not rename without explicit instruction.
